methods.get:
Gets the value associated with the key

:param key: (AssociativeDataWithDefault.KEY) - key
:return: (AssociativeDataWithDefault.VALUE) value associated with the key
methods.getDefault:
Gets the default value for this dataset.

:return: (AssociativeDataWithDefault.VALUE) default value for this dataset
methods.getSpecific:
Gets this dataset's key-value pairs as an AssociativeData dataset.

:return: (io.deephaven.plot.datasets.data.AssociativeData<AssociativeDataWithDefault.KEY,AssociativeDataWithDefault.VALUE>) AssociativeData dataset representing this datasets key-value pairs
methods.isModifiable:
Whether the dataset is modifiable.

:return: (boolean) true if the dataset is modifiable, false if not
methods.put:
Adds the key-value pair to the dataset.

:param key: (AssociativeDataWithDefault.KEY) - key
:param value: (AssociativeDataWithDefault.VALUE) - value
methods.putAll:
Adds all key-value pairs in the map to the dataset.

Note: Java generics information - <K extends AssociativeDataWithDefault.KEY,
V extends AssociativeDataWithDefault.VALUE>

:param values: (java.util.Map<K,V>) - keypair map
methods.set:
Sets this dataset's values equal to the values in another dataset.

:param data: (io.deephaven.plot.datasets.data.AssociativeDataWithDefault<AssociativeDataWithDefault.KEY,AssociativeDataWithDefault.VALUE>) - dataset to get values from.
methods.setDefault:
Defines the default value for this dataset.

:param value: (AssociativeDataWithDefault.VALUE) - default value
methods.setSpecific:
Sets this dataset's key-value pairs.

:param provider: (io.deephaven.plot.datasets.data.AssociativeData<AssociativeDataWithDefault.KEY,AssociativeDataWithDefault.VALUE>) - dataset holding key-value pairs

text:
Dataset which has values associated with keys. When the dataset has no value associated with a given key, it falls
 back to a specified default value.
